y%20content%3A%5Cn%20%20%20%60%60%60bash%5Cn%20%20%20cat%20~%2F.ssh%2Fid_ed25519.pub%5Cn%20%20%20%60%60%60%5Cn%5Cn2.%20Copy%20the%20output%20content%20(starting%20with%20%60ssh-ed25519%60)%5Cn%5Cn3.%20Add%20on%20GitHub%3A%5Cn%20%20%20-%20Go%20to%20**Settings**%20%E2%86%92%20**SSH%20and%20GPG%20keys**%5Cn%20%20%20-%20Click%20**New%20SSH%20key**%5Cn%20%20%20-%20Paste%20the%20public%20key%20content%20and%20save%5Cn%5Cn%3E%20%F0%9F%93%96%20**Detailed%20Tutorial**%3A%20%5BGitHub%20Official%20Documentation%20-%20Adding%20an%20SSH%20Key%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.github.com%2Fen%2Fauthentication%2Fconnecting-to-github-with-ssh%2Fadding-a-new-ssh-key-to-your-github-account)%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Verify%20SSH%20Connection%5Cn%5Cn%60%60%60bash%5Cnssh%20-T%20git%40github.com%5Cn%60%60%60%5Cn%5CnThe%20first%20connection%20will%20prompt%20you%20to%20confirm%20the%20fingerprint.%20Type%20%60yes%60.%20Seeing%20the%20welcome%20message%20indicates%20success.%5Cn%5Cn---%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%20Push%20Code%20to%20GitHub%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Initialize%20Git%20Repository%20(if%20not%20already%20initialized)%5Cn%5Cn%60%60%60bash%5Cncd%20%3C%E4%BD%A0%E7%9A%84%E4%B8%BB%E9%A2%98%E7%9B%AE%E5%BD%95%3E%5Cngit%20init%5Cngit%20add%20-A%5Cngit%20commit%20-m%20%5C%22init%3A%20%E5%88%9D%E5%A7%8B%E5%8C%96%E9%A1%B9%E7%9B%AE%5C%22%5Cn%60%60%60%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Add%20Remote%20Repository%20and%20Push%5Cn%5CnReplace%20%60%3Cusername%3E%60%20and%20%60%3Crepo%3E%60%20with%20your%20GitHub%20username%20and%20repository%20name%3A%5Cn%5Cn%60%60%60bash%5Cngit%20branch%20-M%20main%5Cngit%20remote%20add%20origin%20git%40github.com%3A%3Cusername%3E%2F%3Crepo%3E.git%5Cngit%20push%20-u%20origin%20main%5Cn%60%60%60%5Cn%5CnAfter%20a%20successful%20push%2C%20your%20code%20will%20appear%20in%20the%20%60main%60%20branch%20of%20the%20GitHub%20repository.%5Cn%5Cn---%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%20Configuring%20Nuxt%20Build%5Cn%5Cn%3E%20%E2%9A%A0%EF%B8%8F%20**Note**%3A%20This%20section%20is%20for%20the%20example%20theme%20using%20Nuxt.%20If%20you%20are%