0%60%60%5Cn%5CnThis%20command%20will%20automatically%20create%20the%20%60gh-pages%60%20branch%20and%20push%20the%20static%20files.%5Cn%5Cn---%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%20Enable%20GitHub%20Pages%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Configuring%20Pages%20Settings%5Cn%5Cn1.%20Go%20to%20your%20GitHub%20repository%5Cn2.%20Click%20on%20**Settings**%5Cn3.%20Find%20**Pages**%20in%20the%20left-hand%20menu%5Cn4.%20Configure%20the%20publishing%20source%3A%5Cn%20%20%20-%20**Source**%3A%20Select%20**Deploy%20from%20a%20branch**%5Cn%20%20%20-%20**Branch**%3A%20Select%20**gh-pages**%5Cn%20%20%20-%20**Folder**%3A%20Select%20**%2F%20(root)**%5Cn5.%20Click%20**Save**%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Access%20Your%20Site%5Cn%5CnAfter%20a%20brief%20moment%2C%20GitHub%20will%20provide%20your%20site%20address%3A%5Cn%5Cn%60%60%60txt%5Cnhttps%3A%2F%2F%3Cusername%3E.github.io%2F%3Crepo%3E%2F%5Cn%60%60%60%5Cn%5CnClick%20the%20link%20to%20visit%20your%20blog!%5Cn%5Cn---%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%20Frequently%20Asked%20Questions%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Q%3A%20How%20to%20achieve%20automatic%20deployment%3F%5Cn%5CnA%3A%20You%20can%20use%20GitHub%20Actions%20to%20achieve%20automatic%20build%20and%20deployment.%20Nuxt%20officially%20provides%20example%20workflows.%20For%20details%2C%20refer%20to%20the%20%5BNuxt%20GitHub%20Pages%20Deployment%20Documentation%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fnuxt.com%2Fdeploy%2Fgithub-pages).%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Q%3A%20How%20to%20use%20a%20custom%20domain%3F%5Cn%5CnA%3A%20Add%20a%20custom%20domain%20in%20GitHub%20Pages%20settings%20and%20configure%20DNS%20resolution%20at%20your%20domain%20service%20provider%20to%20point%20to%20GitHub%20Pages.%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Q%3A%20What%20to%20do%20if%20the%20build%20fails%3F%5Cn%5CnA%3A%20I%20don't%20know%5Cn%5CnYour%20blog%20is%20now%20live%20and%20ready%20to%20be%20shared!%20%F0%9F%8E%89%22%7D`
